  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003csection\u003e\n        \n\n    \n\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eYes, we know, HOAs truly do not have a good reputation. It feels like ever neighborhood with an HOA is just getting all of their residents to hemorrhage \u003ca href=\"https://cheezburger.com/41494789/office-worker-discovers-company-is-secretly-tracking-his-location-after-they-force-every-employee-to\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003emoney to fill the pockets of some greedy Karen or Kevin\u003c/a\u003e geezers. Do they even fill the potholes? Do they make sure that one entitled neighbor isn\u0026#39;t building a pool on someone else\u0026#39;s property? Do they clean up graffiti in the neighborhood? Probably not. They just fine people for grass that\u0026#39;s too long and then use that money to take a cruise. \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eBut that was not the original idea for HOAs: They were supposed to be support systems for the neighborhood. And every now and then, we find a story about an HOA that is still, surprisingly, good! \u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\n\u003cul\u003e\n\n    \u003cli\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eThat this \u003ca href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/fuckHOA/comments/1lysuuh/resident_mad_because_my_hoa_would_not_hire_her/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"\u003eRedditor\u0026#39;s\u003c/a\u003e story, for example. Her neighborhood HOA is chill and just there to keep the peace in the neighborhood. However, one resident moves in and starts demanding they make more infractions. So when she started snooping on other people\u0026#39;s properties, the neighborhood finds out she runs her own HOA management company and wants them to be turned over to her so she can charge them up the wazoo! Luckily, this HOA had their residents\u0026#39; back.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10530300160/hC5A47F07\" id=\"_r_a_10530300160\" width=\"800\" height=\"534\" alt=\"Cheezburger Image 10530300160\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n            \u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ci\u003e\u003csub\u003e\u003csup\u003eThe image does not depict the actual subjects of the story. Subjects are models.\u003c/sup\u003e\u003c/sub\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n            \u003cp\u003e\n                                    \u003ch2\u003e\u0026#34;Resident mad because my HOA would not hire her company to run our HOA.\u0026#34;\u003c/h2\u003e\n            \u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10530306560/h8A46E0E0/or-crop-like-keep-costs-down-ran-hoa-ourselves-s-set-up-late-90s-community-built-woman-and\" id=\"_r_a_10530306560\" width=\"800\" height=\"869\" alt=\"I was the prez of our HOA for several years. It was laid back, no snooping for violations or crop like that. To keep costs down, we ran the HOA ourselves. That\u0026#39;s how it was set up in the late 90\u0026#39;s when the community was built. Woman and\" title=\"\u0026#34;Resident mad because my HOA would not hire her company to run our HOA.\u0026#34;\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10530307328/h2591FF09/would-come-our-monthly-meetings-and-say-our-pool-violation-new-code-rules-and-would-have-be-closed\" id=\"_r_a_10530307328\" width=\"800\" height=\"857\" alt=\"hubby move in and she immediately starts the telling everyone how bad the HOA is managing everything. She would come to our monthly meetings and say that our pool was in violation of new code rules and would have to be closed. We\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10530306816/h80B9FDB4/at-meeting-she-wrong-she-continued-do-this-and-continue-find-out-every-time-she-making-stuff-up\" id=\"_r_a_10530306816\" width=\"800\" height=\"710\" alt=\"would research it find out she was wrong and alert all the people that were at the meeting that she was wrong. She continued to do this and we continue to find out every time that she was making stuff up.\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n    \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10530307584/h96D0E51E/all-our-hoa-responsibilities-her-company-somewhere-range-700-1000-month-going-meetings-and-openly\" id=\"_r_a_10530307584\" width=\"800\" height=\"912\" alt=\"Turns out she runs an HOA management company and wanted us to turn over all of our HOA responsibilities to her company for somewhere in the range of $700 to $1,000 a month. When going to meetings and openly\" title=\"\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEAAAAALAAAAAABAAEAAAI=\"/\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/li\u003e\n    \u003cli\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://i.chzbgr.com/full/10530307072/hFC3DB2DB/violations-and-emailing-or-texting-with-photos-informed-her-if-shes-going-on-other-peoples-property\" id=\"_r_a_10530307072\" width=\"800\" height=\"881\" alt=\"lying about i